---
import Layout from '~/layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import DarkHero from '~/components/widgets/DarkHero.astro';

const metadata = {
  title: 'Terms of Service | SimpleScheduleAI',
  description: 'The terms that govern your use of SimpleScheduleAI.com and our nurse scheduling service.',
};

const effectiveDate = 'March 5, 2026';
const contactEmail = 'support@simplescheduleai.com';
---

<Layout metadata={metadata}>
  <!-- Dark Hero -->
  <DarkHero badge="Legal" title="Terms of Service" subtitle={metadata.description} />

  <!-- Content -->
  <section class="bg-page">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-4 py-20 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 lg:py-28">
      <p class="text-sm text-muted mb-10">Effective date: {effectiveDate}</p>

      <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl space-y-10 text-default">
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">Agreement to these terms</h2>
          <p class="mt-3 leading-relaxed">
            By using SimpleScheduleAI.com or engaging with our scheduling service, you agree to these Terms of Service.
            If you are using our service on behalf of a hospital or organization, you represent that you have authority
            to bind that organization to these terms.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">Who we are and what we do</h2>
          <p class="mt-3 leading-relaxed">
            SimpleScheduleAI provides an assisted nurse scheduling service for Critical Access Hospitals. We help build
            draft schedules based on your inputs and constraints, validate those drafts for coverage, gaps, and common
            failure points, and return a clean, review-ready version for your team's approval.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-3 leading-relaxed">
            We are a scheduling support service. We are not a staffing agency, a healthcare provider, an HR system, or a
            software platform. We do not publish, implement, or finalize any schedule without your team's explicit
            approval.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">The pilot program</h2>
          <p class="mt-3 leading-relaxed">The free 60-day pilot is a managed service engagement. During the pilot:</p>
          <ul class="mt-4 space-y-2">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="mt-2 w-1.5 h-1.5 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-primary"></span>
              <span>There is no cost to your organization for the 60-day period</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="mt-2 w-1.5 h-1.5 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-primary"></span>
              <span>We work within your existing scheduling format and tools</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="mt-2 w-1.5 h-1.5 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-primary"></span>
              <span>Your team retains full authority to approve, modify, or reject any draft schedule we produce</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="mt-2 w-1.5 h-1.5 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-primary"></span>
              <span>Either party may end the engagement at any time</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
          <p class="mt-4 leading-relaxed">
            After the pilot period, we will conduct a strategic review together. If you want to continue, we will build
            a plan at that point. There is no automatic renewal, no surprise billing, and no obligation beyond the pilot
            itself.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">Your responsibilities</h2>
          <p class="mt-3 leading-relaxed">You are responsible for:</p>
          <ul class="mt-4 space-y-2">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="mt-2 w-1.5 h-1.5 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-primary"></span>
              <span>Providing accurate scheduling inputs, constraints, and staff information</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="mt-2 w-1.5 h-1.5 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-primary"></span>
              <span>Reviewing all draft schedules before they are used operationally</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="mt-2 w-1.5 h-1.5 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-primary"></span>
              <span
                >Ensuring compliance with applicable labor laws, union agreements, licensing requirements, and internal
                policies</span
              >
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="mt-2 w-1.5 h-1.5 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-primary"></span>
              <span
                >Making final decisions about your scheduling. Our drafts are inputs for your review, not final outputs</span
              >
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">Not medical, legal, or HR advice</h2>
          <p class="mt-3 leading-relaxed">
            Nothing we produce constitutes medical advice, legal advice, or human resources guidance. Our scheduling
            drafts are operational tools to reduce workload. Your clinical and administrative leadership is responsible
            for ensuring schedules meet patient care standards and regulatory requirements.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">No patient data</h2>
          <p class="mt-3 leading-relaxed">
            Do not share patient health information with us through this website or as part of the scheduling service.
            Our service is scoped to nurse scheduling data only. We are not set up to serve as a HIPAA Business
            Associate in the context of this website or the scheduling pilot.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">Intellectual property</h2>
          <p class="mt-3 leading-relaxed">
            The content on this website, including copy, design, and tools, is owned by SimpleScheduleAI. You may not
            reproduce or redistribute it without our permission. Scheduling drafts we produce for your organization
            during the pilot are yours to use for your internal scheduling purposes.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">Limitation of liability</h2>
          <p class="mt-3 leading-relaxed">
            SimpleScheduleAI provides scheduling assistance in good faith based on the information you provide. We are
            not liable for scheduling errors that result from inaccurate inputs, failure to review our drafts, or
            decisions made outside our recommendations. Our total liability in any circumstances is limited to the fees
            paid to us in the most recent 30 days, which during the free pilot period is zero.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">No warranties</h2>
          <p class="mt-3 leading-relaxed">
            This website and the scheduling service are provided as-is. We make no guarantees about uptime, error-free
            operation, or specific scheduling outcomes. We will work diligently to deliver high-quality drafts, but
            scheduling is complex and human judgment remains essential.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">Governing law</h2>
          <p class="mt-3 leading-relaxed">
            These terms are governed by the laws of the State of Texas, without regard to conflict of law principles.
            Any disputes will be resolved in Texas.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">Changes to these terms</h2>
          <p class="mt-3 leading-relaxed">
            We may update these terms as the service evolves. Material changes will be reflected in an updated effective
            date. Continued use of the service after changes are posted constitutes acceptance of the revised terms.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Dark contact band -->
  <section class="bg-slate-950 dark:bg-black">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-4 py-20 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 lg:py-28">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl">
        <p class="mb-4 text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-blue-400">Contact</p>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white">Questions about these terms?</h2>
        <p class="mt-4 text-gray-400">If you have questions about these Terms of Service, reach out directly.</p>
        <p class="mt-6 text-lg font-medium text-blue-400">
          <a href={`mailto:${contactEmail}`} class="hover:text-blue-300">{contactEmail}</a>
        </p>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-gray-500">SimpleScheduleAI, Remote, US</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
